{\par \b Syntax:}\par simult(Mtrx(A),Mtrx(B))\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Returns the matrix where the column of index k is solution of A*X=column of index k of B (=B[0..nr-1,k..k] with nr=number of rows of B)\par
{\par \b Example:}\par simult([[3,1],[3,2]],[[-2],[2]]) returns [[-2],[4]]\par }